
[1]scantiness

   SCANT'INESS, n.

   1. Narrowness; want of space or compass; as the scantiness of our
   heroic verse.

   2. Want of amplitude, greatness or abundance; limited extent.

   Alexander was much troubled at the scantiness of nature itself.

   3. Want of fullness; want of sufficiency; as the scantiness of
   supplies.
